On 5/30/19 7:49 AM, David wrote:
> So, anyone ever use this feature?

Yes.  I have been on both sides of disk / file system quota,=20
occasionally at the same time.

I remember them being applied when I was in school.

I applied them to mail servers I administered (50 MB quota).

I think I even used a combination of soft (50 MB) and hard (100 MB)=20
quotas.  I really liked the soft/hard pair because someone could go over =

their quota for up to 7 days (?) until they hit the hard quota.  This=20
gave some buffer for busy weekends and vacation time.

I also applied a quota to myself (and the other admins) specifically so=20
that we couldn't accidentally fill the file system and DoS our users.  I =

think I gave us a 1 or 2 GB quota.  I do remember raising it once or=20
twice for specific things.  It did save our collected back sides=20
multiple times too.



--=20
Grant. . . .
